{
  "texts": [
    "Artificial intelligence-based organizational knowledge management can generate automated responses to employees' inquiries about their issues and problems in the same manner it facilitates students using chatbots (Kumar et al., 2021).",
    "Unlike human experts, Chatbots have no limitation on time, location, and number of queries, allowing efficient and effective knowledge sharing (Narendra et al., 2017).",
    "They can complete physical and mental activities far better and faster than humans; however, they lack wisdom and cognitive awareness (Sanzogni et al., 2017).",
    "Chatbots can give human-like interaction and outperform the traditional techniques of knowledge externalization, i.e., concept maps, discussion, and questionnaire surveys, by using its vast knowledge repository (Narendra et al., 2017).",
    "However, keeping a record of employees' dialogue with the Chatbots is essential."
  ]
}